<paragraph blockId="98.[151,1437,798,1365]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,216,1087,1113]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Note:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[224,446,1087,1113]" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Amblyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtum">
<emphasis box="[224,446,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Amblyomma hirtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not included as valid in 
<bibRefCitation author="Keirans, J. E." box="[748,919,1087,1113]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref217609" refString="Keirans, J. E. (1992) Systematics of the Ixodida (Argasidae, Ixodidae, Nuttalliellidae): an overview and some problems. In: Fivaz, B., Petney, T. &amp; Horak, I. (Eds.), Tick vector biology. Medical and veterinary aspects. Springer-Verlag. Berlin, New York and othercities, pp. 1 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 3 - 642 - 76643 - 5 _ 1" type="book chapter" year="1992">Keirans (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, probably because he overlooked this species, whose illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation author="Neumann, L. G." box="[397,587,1123,1150]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" pagination="195 - 219" refId="ref233460" refString="Neumann, L. G. (1906) Notes sur les Ixodides. IV. Archives de Parasitologie, 10, 195 - 219." type="journal article" year="1906">
<taxonomicName authority="Guglielmone &amp; Petney &amp; Robbins, 2020" authorityName="Guglielmone &amp; Petney &amp; Robbins" authorityYear="2020" box="[397,506,1123,1149]" pageId="98" pageNumber="289" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. n." subGenus="Neumann">Neumann</taxonomicName>
(1906)
</bibRefCitation>
resemble the figure of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keirans, Hoogstraal and Clifford" authorityYear="1973" box="[846,1130,1123,1149]" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Amblyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macfarlandi">
<emphasis box="[846,1130,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Amblyomma macfarlandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Keirans, J. E. &amp; Hoogstraal, H. &amp; Clifford, C. M." pageId="98" pageNumber="99" pagination="673 - 688" refId="ref218941" refString="Keirans, J. E., Hoogstraal, H. &amp; Clifford, C. M. (1973) The Amblyomma (Acarina: Ixodidae) parasitic on giant tortoises (Reptilia: Testudinidae) of the Galapagos Islands. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 66, 673 - 688. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 66.3.673" type="journal article" year="1973">
Keirans 
<emphasis box="[1381,1437,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">et al.</emphasis>
(1973)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, J.E. Keirans in 
<bibRefCitation author="Guglielmone, A. A. &amp; Estrada-Pena, A. &amp; Keirans, J. E. &amp; Robbins, R. G." box="[523,812,1159,1185]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" refId="ref204889" refString="Guglielmone, A. A., Estrada-Pena, A., Keirans, J. E. &amp; Robbins, R. G. (2003) Ticks (Acari: Ixodida) of the Neotropical Zoogeographic Region. Special Publication of the Integrated Consortium on Ticks and Tick-Borne Diseases- 2. Integrated Consortium on Ticks and Tick-Borne Diseases, Atalanta, Houten, 173 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Guglielmone 
<emphasis box="[675,731,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
stated, after checking the 
<typeStatus box="[1101,1160,1159,1185]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">types</typeStatus>
of both taxa, that female 
<taxonomicName box="[151,374,1195,1221]" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Amblyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtum">
<emphasis box="[151,374,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Amblyomma hirtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possess very large porose areas and long setae on the dorsum, with whitish-ivory ornamentation confined to the scapular region, while the male of 
<taxonomicName box="[756,977,1231,1257]" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Amblyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtum">
<emphasis box="[756,977,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Amblyomma hirtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much smaller than that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keirans, Hoogstraal and Clifford" authorityYear="1973" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Amblyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macfarlandi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Amblyomma macfarlandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and its dentition is 2/2, whereas that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keirans, Hoogstraal and Clifford" authorityYear="1973" box="[732,1015,1267,1293]" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Amblyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macfarlandi">
<emphasis box="[732,1015,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Amblyomma macfarlandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 3/3. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName box="[1216,1437,1267,1293]" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Amblyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtum">
<emphasis box="[1216,1437,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Amblyomma hirtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keirans, Hoogstraal and Clifford" authorityYear="1973" box="[200,485,1303,1329]" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Amblyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macfarlandi">
<emphasis box="[200,485,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Amblyomma macfarlandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are regarded as valid here. 
<bibRefCitation author="Santos Dias, J. A. T." box="[799,1028,1302,1329]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref243153" refString="Santos Dias, J. A. T. (1958 c) Notas ixodologicas. V. Acerca de alguns ixodideos do Museu do Hamburgo. Memorias e Estudos d o Museu Zoologico da Universidade de Coimbra, 253, 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1958">Santos Dias (1958c)</bibRefCitation>
treats 
<taxonomicName box="[1105,1328,1303,1329]" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Amblyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtum">
<emphasis box="[1105,1328,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Amblyomma hirtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Robinson" authorityYear="1926" box="[252,488,1339,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Amblyomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosum">
<emphasis box="[252,488,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Amblyomma pilosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but both species are valid, as discussed in 
<bibRefCitation author="Guglielmone, A. A. &amp; Estrada-Pena, A. &amp; Keirans, J. E. &amp; Robbins, R. G." box="[974,1268,1339,1365]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" refId="ref204889" refString="Guglielmone, A. A., Estrada-Pena, A., Keirans, J. E. &amp; Robbins, R. G. (2003) Ticks (Acari: Ixodida) of the Neotropical Zoogeographic Region. Special Publication of the Integrated Consortium on Ticks and Tick-Borne Diseases- 2. Integrated Consortium on Ticks and Tick-Borne Diseases, Atalanta, Houten, 173 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Guglielmone 
<emphasis box="[1127,1183,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
